==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swough
<hw>Swough</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Swoon</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sound; a groan; a moan; a
sough.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He sigheth with full many a sorry <qex>swough</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A swoon.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swound</ent>⟦br⟧
